Katy Perry lit up Arizona with a show-stopping performance during the half-time show at the Super Bowl on Sunday night.

The 30-year-old Californian provided the entertainment during the interval of the New England Patriots’ clash with the Seattle Seahawks at the University of Phoenix Stadium in Glendale.

Perry has had two No 1 studio albums in the United States as well as nine No 1 hit singles since bursting onto the scene in 2008.

